TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bruce, Neil
AU  - Waldman, Michael
T1  - The Rotten-Kid Theorem Meets the Samaritan's Dilemma*
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937823
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 105
IS  - 1
SP  - 155
EP  - 165
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A familiar result in the economic theory of the family is Becker's rotten-kid theorem. This theorem states that altruism by a family member will lead other selfish members to act efficiently from the family viewpoint. We extend Becker's one-period model to two periods and show that parental altruism can result in an inefficiency known in other contexts as the Samaritan's dilemma. Implications of this for transfer arrangements within the family and for the Ricardian equivalence theorem are drawn.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937823
ER  - 



